Cell.Data: Identifies the specification of content and rules that apply to the transaction.

Identifies the BII profile or business process context in which the transaction appears. There are two ProfileIDs defined for the Advanced Despatch Advice. One profile is used when the receiver of the Despatch Advice is expected to return a response message, the other is used when no response message is used. Possible choices are: "urn:fdc:peppol.eu:logistics:bis:despatch_advice_only:1" and "urn:fdc:peppol.eu:logistics:bis:despatch_advice_w_receipt_advice:1"

An transaction instance must contain an identifier. The identifier enables positive referencing the document instance for various purposes including referencing between transactions that are part of the same process.
The date when the Advanced Despatch Advice is issued. Format = "YYYY-MM-DD". Together with ID and IssueTime the IssueDate forms the identity of the Version of the Advanced Despatch Advice.
The time when the Advanced Despatch Advice is issued. Format = "hh:mm:ss+timezone". Timezone is optional to use. If omitted, the local timezone where the document was issued should be assumed.
A code signifying the status of the Despatch Advice. Default is Original (9)
A code signifying the type of the Despatch Advice. Default is Advice of despatch of goods (1)
A textual note for the despatch as whole.

The type of reference. Must me part of UNCL1001. At least one of Document Type Code and Document Type must be used.
The type of reference that cannot be specified by a code. At least one of Document Type Code and Document Type must be used.
Group to describe an attached document. An attachment can refer to an external document or be included with the document being exchanged.

The role is carried out by the supplier or on behalf of the supplier. The real ship-from address must be provided in the Despatch Address when the Advanced Despatch Advice describes a movement.

Used to indicate that the ID is in the GINC (Global Identification Number for Consignment) format. This number identifies a consignment, which is a logical grouping of goods (one or more logistics units) transferred to a freight forwarder to be transported for a specific journey. The consignment number must be allocated by a freight forwarder (or a carrier acting as a freight forwarder) or a consignor, but only if prior agreement of the freight forwarder is given.
